.SH NAME
bb-pr-close - Close a pull request without merging it


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbb pr close  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Close a pull request without merging it. In Bitbucket Cloud this maps to declining the pull request. Accepts a numeric ID, pull request URL, or pull request comment URL.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for close

.PP
\fB--host\fP=""
	Bitbucket host to use

.PP
\fB--jq\fP=""
	Filter JSON output using a jq expression

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=""]
	Output JSON with the specified comma-separated fields, or '*' for all fields

.PP
\fB--repo\fP=""
	Bitbucket repository target as , /, or a repository URL

.PP
\fB--workspace\fP=""
	Optional workspace slug used only to disambiguate a bare repository target


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--no-prompt\fP[=false]
	Do not prompt for missing input, even in an interactive terminal


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bb pr close 1
  bb pr close 1 --repo workspace-slug/repo-slug
  bb pr close https://bitbucket.org/workspace-slug/repo-slug/pull-requests/1 --json
  bb pr close https://bitbucket.org/workspace-slug/repo-slug/pull-requests/1#comment-15
.EE


